<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-359-402  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 359 402.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  April 16 1990 v218 n16 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI acquires rival Telecom*USA to strengthen market position.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Karpinski, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp will acquire rival long-distance carrierTelecom*USA for $1.25 billion.andP;  MCI will purchase all outstandingstock from Telecom, the fourth largest carrier in the country, for$42 a share.andP;  Prior to the announcement Telecom stock was tradingat $21.87 a share.andP;  Telecom had 1989 revenues of $713 million,grabbing a little over one percent of the long-distance market.andO;MCI controls approximately 12 percent of the total market, and theacquisition will add about 600,000 accounts to MCI's customerbase.andP;  MCI will gain customers in small to mid-level businesses,an area where it has been weak, as well as obtaining some 3000miles of fiber network in the Southeast and Midwest.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (acquisitions and mergers)Telecom*USA Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     AcquisitionTelephone CompaniesSecurities TransferFinancial Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>